---
import Page from '~/layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page
  title="Documentation — DataSUS ETL"
  description="Technical reference: CLI, Python API, architecture, schemas."
  locale="en"
  currentKey="docs"
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-24">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-muted">
      <span class="pill pill-brand"><span class="pill-dot"></span>Docs</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="mt-5 text-display-lg text-text font-semibold">Technical reference.</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lead text-muted max-w-prose-tech leading-relaxed">
      Everything a developer or data engineer needs to automate, embed,
      or extend DataSUS ETL. The desktop app is a convenience — the
      engine is the CLI, the Python API, and the partitioned parquet
      store underneath.
    </p>

    <nav class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <a href="./cli/" class="card card-interactive p-6 block group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="mono-val text-xs text-brand border border-brand/30 bg-brand/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">01</span>
          <span class="label-stamp-strong">CLI reference</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-display text-text font-semibold group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">Command line</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <code class="font-mono text-text bg-surface-2 border border-border px-1 rounded text-[0.85em]">pipeline</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-text bg-surface-2 border border-border px-1 rounded text-[0.85em]">update</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-text bg-surface-2 border border-border px-1 rounded text-[0.85em]">status</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-text bg-surface-2 border border-border px-1 rounded text-[0.85em]">db</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-text bg-surface-2 border border-border px-1 rounded text-[0.85em]">ui</code>.
          Shared flags, exit codes, scripting recipes.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./python-api/" class="card card-interactive p-6 block group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="mono-val text-xs text-brand border border-brand/30 bg-brand/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">02</span>
          <span class="label-stamp-strong">Python API</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-display text-text font-semibold group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">As a library</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          The same pipeline imported into your own Python code. Useful
          when you want the ETL inside a larger workflow (Airflow,
          Prefect, notebook-driven analysis).
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./architecture/" class="card card-interactive p-6 block group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="mono-val text-xs text-brand border border-brand/30 bg-brand/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">03</span>
          <span class="label-stamp-strong">Architecture</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-display text-text font-semibold group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">How the pieces fit</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Path resolution, legacy migration, SPA bundling,
          tkinter-in-subprocess, and the release pipeline.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./schemas/" class="card card-interactive p-6 block group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="mono-val text-xs text-brand border border-brand/30 bg-brand/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">04</span>
          <span class="label-stamp-strong">Schemas</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-display text-text font-semibold group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">Subsystem columns</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          SIHSUS and SIM column lists, types, enrichments. What is
          identical to the DATASUS original, what has been cleaned, and
          where you can read the SQL that did it.
        </p>
      </a>
    </nav>

    <aside class="note mt-12">
      <div class="label-stamp text-brand">Maintainer note</div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted max-w-prose-tech leading-relaxed">
        The docs below are the user-facing summary. For the canonical
        source of truth on any detail, read the repository — every code
        path referenced here is linked directly to its file and line on
        GitHub.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</Page>
